<item>
            <title>[LU-9292] mount.lustre doesn&apos;t handle partitioned MD arrays correctly</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9292</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The set_blockdev_tunables function in lustre/utils/mount_lustre.c doesn&apos;t correctly parse the newer names of partitioned MD devices (e.g., /dev/md0p2) .. it looks like it&apos;s written to parse the older partitioned MD devices (e.g., /dev/md_d2p3).&lt;br/&gt;
This means that MD partions like /dev/md0p2 do not receive MD-level tunings that non-partitioned MD devices get (specifically stripe_cache_size), leading to a large performance hit.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
